subsubsections.text_content:
When a malicious container escapes isolation, it can gain full control over the underlying host and cause any of the below serious threats.
An attacker would gain the ability to:
-	mount attacks on host OS or compromise host OS functionalities;
-	compromise the confidentiality & integrity of co-hosted containers and tenants;
-	introduce new vulnerabilities.
Such threats can have a devastating effect in multi-tenant deployments. A malicious container breakout of one tenant can potentially comprise all co-hosted containers of other tenants.
